  Dex, Agi, Str are the only other REAL options. If you maxxed your INT, then you only have 5 points left anyway. I would put it in the category of your choice. I can remember that I didnt max Niti's Int. Instead of putting her Int at 142, I made it 132, and spread the other points out across the board ( I even put 5 in STA, which is why Im saying dont bother).<br>
   You will be stepping in to take some of the damage for your pet, and to insure that both of you survive the fight. So every offensive stat point you raise will help, albeit in a small way. I helped tank for my pet up till around L36.<br>
   Its VERY important for ANY caster to try to keep their Defense ability maxxed. I also kept my Offense maxxed, and trained my 1hb and pierce skills in combat. I wielded procing weapons to help tank even...an Obsidian shard which procs a 30DD fire based, and the Staff or Writhing which procs at L28 a 48DD magic based. The Shard procd early, round L15 or so, and procd often. Good lil piercer. But if you keep your 1hb up, u can do 19dmg a swing max. 2HB in my opinion is a waste of time for mages, taking away a free hand for somekind of item that will help out alot.<br>
